@node Einleitung
@{b}@{fg shine}Introduction:
-------------@{fg text}@{ub}

  @{b}Welcome to Cybermagic@{ub}

  Cybermagic is a screenblanker for Amiga computer with
  PPC-Board und 3D Graphixcard.

  @{b}The blanker currently has the following modules:@{ub}

  @{i}( This modules run with a 68020 and a GFX-Card without a 3D-Chip )@{ui}

  - Black
  - Worms
  - Puzzle
  - Moire
  - Pendulum

  @{i}( This modules needs a PPC and a 3D-GFX-Card )@{ui}

  - Cube
  - Morph
  - Gears
  - Starlight
  - In&Out

  Cybermagic also supports the DPMS energy-saving method of modern monitors.

  This Blanker is a system-friendly commodity, you have also keyboard shortcuts
  and a AREXX-Port.

@endnode

@node Systemanforderungen
@{b}@{fg shine}Requirements:
-------------@{fg text}@{ub}

  @{b}The minimum requirements are:@{ub}

  - 68020
  - Cybergrapics V3 and a graphiccard
  - AmigaOS3.0

  @{b}For all modules:@{ub}

  - PPC processor
  - Cybergraphics V3 and a graphiccard with 3D-Chip
  - WarpOS4
  - Warp3D2.0
  - Stormmesa3.1


    You can download WarpOS, Warp3D and Stormmesa under http:www.haage-partner.com


  @{b}Additional:@{ub}

  - Superplay.library 7.2 or higher, for sound output,
    you can find it at the Aminet in the drawer mus/play
    or on the AminetCD 21. [SPLibUsr.lha]

  - DeliTracker2
    you can find it on every AminetCD.

  - HippoPlayer 2.44

  - ARexx for the sound output beyond DeliTracker2,
    and the steering of the Cybermagic mainprogram.


    @{b}@{i}Cybermagic needs always a screen deep of 15Bit or higher.@{ui}@{ub}

@endnode

@node Installation
@{b}@{fg shine}Installation:
-------------@{fg text}@{ub}

  Start the installation program "INSTALL" and make
  the installation as your desired.

  If you have only a 68k processor install the STANDARD module.

  For the 3D module you need @{b}WarpOSV4@{ub}, @{b}Warp3D2.0@{ub} and @{b}Stormmesa3.1@{ub}.
  !! Install the PPC versions of Warp3D and Stormmesa !!

@endnode

