@node MainWindow
@{b}@{fg shine}Setup Window:
-------------@{fg text}@{ub}

  In the first line of the window there are 4 buttons.
  The description is from left to right.

  @{i}1. Start the opposed blanker.
  2. Save the settings.
  3. Opens the settings of the opposed blanker.
  4. Opens this Guide.@{ui}

  After that there are 4 index cards.

  @{i}1. Choose the blanker modul.
  2. Choose the sound modul.
  3. Sets the timer for the blanker start.
     Sets the timer for the DPMS function.
     The DPMS time is added to the blanker time.
  4. Sets the player for the sound.@{ui}

  In the first and the second index card you have the possibility of
  a random selection.

@endnode

@node ToolTypes
@{b}@{fg shine}ToolTypes:
----------@{fg text}@{ub}

  Following ToolTypes are available:

  @{fg shine}CX_PRIORITY@{fg text}      Sets the Task-Priority of Cybermagic.
  @{fg shine}CX_POPUP@{fg text}         The Item <YES> opens the setup window by
                   every start of Cybermagic.
                   <NO> opens the window by the second start
                   of Cybermagic.
  @{fg shine}CX_POPKEY@{fg text}        The Hotkey pushbutton-combination for
                   opening the  setup window.
                   <alt F1> is opposed.
  @{fg shine}MODUL_POPKEY@{fg text}     The Hotkey pushbutton-combination for
                   starting the opposed blanker modul.
                   <alt F2> is opposed.
  @{fg shine}CLICKTOFRONT@{fg text}     <YES> enable the window click
                   to front function, <NO> disable it.
  @{fg shine}NO8BIT@{fg text}           <YES> enable the no 8 Bit function.
                   The Blanker will not turn on if a 8 Bit screen in front.

@endnode

@node ARexx
@{b}@{fg shine}ARexx:
------@{fg text}@{ub}

  Following ARexx Commandos are available:

  @{fg shine}CMShow@{fg text}          Open the  setup window.
  @{fg shine}CMHide@{fg text}          Close the setup window.

  @{fg shine}CMEnable@{fg text}        Enable Cybermagic.
  @{fg shine}CMDisable@{fg text}       Disable Cybermagic.
  @{fg shine}CMQuit@{fg text}          Quit Cybermagic.

  @{fg shine}CMStart@{fg text}         Start the opposed blanker modul.

  @{fg shine}CMClickON@{fg text}       Enable the ClickToFront funktion.
  @{fg shine}CMClickOFF@{fg text}      Disable the ClickToFront funktion.

  @{fg shine}CMNo8BitON@{fg text}      Enable the No8Bit funktion.
  @{fg shine}CMNo8BitOFF@{fg text}     Disable the No8Bit funktion.

@endnode

@node Fehler
@{b}@{fg shine}Bugs:
-----@{fg text}@{ub}

  - A known bug concerned the sound output.
    There is no check if the sound chip is occupied
    to an other program. This is the reason why it is
    possible that two programs play sound at the same time.

  - Joystick input will be not detect, thats the
    reason why the blanker turn on during you play a game.

@endnode

